headline: Interactive Brokers trumps Q2 estimates on trading surge, shares jump
summary: Investing.com -- Interactive Brokers Group (NASDAQ:IBKR) on Thursday reported second-quarter earnings and revenue that beat Wall Street estimates, driven by a jump in customer trading activity and steady gains in net interest income. Shares popped nearly 5% in premarket trading Friday.
